  "pull_request": {
    "id": 3517056176,
    "title": "Drop Python 3.9, add Python 3.14 support",
    "body": "This updates the repository’s declared/tested Python support to include 3.14 and aligns the surrounding tooling/docs metadata with that support level. It also adjusts request tests for Python 3.14’s event-loop behavior without changing runtime code.\n\n- **Packaging and support metadata**\n  - Add the `Programming Language :: Python :: 3.14` classifier in `pyproject.toml`\n  - Extend `.python-version` to include `3.14` so multi-version checks exercise it\n\n- **Docs and tooling alignment**\n  - Move docs-related Python pins from `3.13` to `3.14` in:\n    - `.readthedocs.yml`\n    - `scripts/docs`\n    - `scripts/serve`\n\n- **Request test compatibility on 3.14**\n  - Keep `pybotters/request.py` unchanged\n  - Update `tests/test_request.py` to pass an explicit mock loop when constructing standalone `ClientRequest` instances outside an active event loop\n\n```python\nreq = ClientRequest(\n    method,\n    url,\n    params=None,\n    headers=None,\n    data=data,\n    auth=None,\n    loop=Mock(),\n)\n```",
    "created_at": "2026-04-11T06:08:30Z",
    "merged_at": "2026-04-11T06:18:26Z",
